{"parse":{"title":"The Armenian Genocide (film)","pageid":4785726,"revid":858046718,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-style: italic; background: #CCCCFF; padding: 0.25em 1em; line-height: 1.5em;\">The Armenian Genocide</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:The_Armenian_Genocide_(2006_film_poster).png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The Armenian Genocide (2006 film poster).png\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/30/The_Armenian_Genocide_%282006_film_poster%29.png/250px-The_Armenian_Genocide_%282006_film_poster%29.png\" width=\"250\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/30/The_Armenian_Genocide_%282006_film_poster%29.png 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"258\" data-file-height=\"386\" /></a><div>Theatrical release poster</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Written by</th><td>\nAndrew Goldberg</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Directed by</th><td class=\"attendee\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Andrew_Goldberg_(director)\" title=\"Andrew Goldberg (director)\">Andrew Goldberg</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country of origin</th><td>\nUnited States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original <span class=\"nowrap\">language(s)</span></th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;background: #CCCCFF; padding: 0.25em 1em; line-height: 1.5em;\">Production</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span class=\"nowrap\">Producer(s)</span></th><td>\nAndrew Goldberg<br /><a href=\"/wiki/Oregon_Public_Broadcasting\" title=\"Oregon Public Broadcasting\">Oregon Public Broadcasting</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Running time</th><td>\n60 minutes</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;background: #CCCCFF; padding: 0.25em 1em; line-height: 1.5em;\">Release</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original network</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/PBS\" title=\"PBS\">PBS</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original release</th><td><div class=\"plainlist\">\n<ul><li>April&#160;17,&#160;2006<span style=\"display:none\">&#160;(<span class=\"bday dtstart published updated\">2006-04-17</span>)</span></li>\n<li class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></li>\n<li class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></li>\n<li class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></li>\n<li class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></li></ul>\n</div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Armenian Genocide</b></i> is a 2006 television documentary film exploring the <a href=\"/wiki/Ottoman_Empire\" title=\"Ottoman Empire\">Ottoman Empire</a> killings of more than one million <a href=\"/wiki/Armenians\" title=\"Armenians\">Armenians</a> during <a href=\"/wiki/World_War_I\" title=\"World War I\">World War I</a>.  The documentary was broadcast by most 348 PBS affiliate stations on April 17, 2006.\n</p><p>Because of the controversial nature of the subject in <a href=\"/wiki/Genocide_denial\" title=\"Genocide denial\">Turkey</a>, PBS attempted to give both sides a voice and produced a four expert panel discussion to be aired immediately afterwards.  However, due to an intense lobbying effort by Armenian groups and some members of <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Congress\" title=\"United States Congress\">Congress</a>, the follow-up panel discussion was cancelled on a third of those stations broadcasting the documentary over concerns of offending human rights groups and the descendants of <a href=\"/wiki/Armenian_Genocide\" title=\"Armenian Genocide\">Armenian Genocide</a> survivors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Produced in conjunction with <a href=\"/wiki/Oregon_Public_Broadcasting\" title=\"Oregon Public Broadcasting\">Oregon Public Broadcasting</a>, it was written and directed by <a href=\"/wiki/Andrew_Goldberg_(director)\" title=\"Andrew Goldberg (director)\">Andrew Goldberg</a> (who also directed <i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Armenians:_A_Story_of_Survival&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"The Armenians: A Story of Survival (page does not exist)\">The Armenians: A Story of Survival</a></i>) and narrated by <a href=\"/wiki/Hollywood\" title=\"Hollywood\">Hollywood</a> celebrities <a href=\"/wiki/Orlando_Bloom\" title=\"Orlando Bloom\">Orlando Bloom</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Ed_Harris\" title=\"Ed Harris\">Ed Harris</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Laura_Linney\" title=\"Laura Linney\">Laura Linney</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Jared_Leto\" title=\"Jared Leto\">Jared Leto</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Julianna_Margulies\" title=\"Julianna Margulies\">Julianna Margulies</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Natalie_Portman\" title=\"Natalie Portman\">Natalie Portman</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Armenian_Genocide_(film)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Armenian_Genocide\" title=\"Armenian Genocide\">Armenian Genocide</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Armenian_Genocide_in_culture\" title=\"Armenian Genocide in culture\">Armenian Genocide in culture</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_American_films_of_2006\" title=\"List of American films of 2006\">List of American films of 2006</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Armenian_Genocide_(film)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Alessandra Stanley, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/17/arts/television/17stan.html\">A PBS Documentary Makes Its Case for the Armenian Genocide, With or Without a Debate</a>, <i>The New York Times</i>, April 17, 2006, <i>Accessed April 17, 2006</i></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Armenian_Genocide_(film)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.twocatstv.com/armenian-genocide\">Armenian Genocide, Two Cats Productions</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0472044/\"><i>The Armenian Genocide</i></a> on <a href=\"/wiki/IMDb\" title=\"IMDb\">IMDb</a>&#32;</li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Historicalfilm.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Historicalfilm.png/30px-Historicalfilm.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Historicalfilm.png/45px-Historicalfilm.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Historicalfilm.png/60px-Historicalfilm.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"128\" data-file-height=\"128\" /></a></td><td><i>This article about a historical documentary film is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=The_Armenian_Genocide_(film)&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plai